cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on using deep learning to analyze X-ray images for heart disease classification, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep learning techniques to train the model, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
- cs.MED (Medical Imaging): The paper deals with medical imaging data (X-ray images) and aims to classify heart diseases, which falls under the domain of medical imaging. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses AI techniques (deep learning) to solve a medical problem (heart disease classification). 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with extracting information from medical images (X-ray) to classify heart diseases, which falls under the domain of information retrieval.
